Version 1.8.0

• In-app notifications: In the Netherlands we say 'Oranje Boven' or 'Orange on Top'. Well that doesn't really count for our national football team anymore, but it does for our app (sort of)! You'll now be able to see important notifications, in orange, at the top of the Booking and Messages icons. Plus, they'll guide you to where your attention is needed.
• Add additional drivers: So your friend riding shotgun is constantly looking whether you're driving skills are good enough to bring them home safe and sound? Give 'em the wheel. Add additional drivers to your booking and go Dutch.
• Predefined messages: So you found a car, but you're at a loss for words? No worries, we got you! Send predefined messages when making a rental request. Like birthday cards, we'll help you out with the cheesy stuff, you just have to make it personal.
• Minor bug fixes: Here's a short story. Quit bugging me said the SnappCar users. Ok, said the developers.

Version 1.9.1

• Performance and stability improvements

Version 1.9.0

• Register or log in - Green lights everywhere! Whether you're looking for a car or renting one out, everyone's now able to log in or register with the App.

• Extend a booking - Extending your booking is a lot like owning a stretch Hummer, you don't always need it but sweet baby cheeses is it cool to have one at hand. Visit your Booking Details to request an Extension and stretch your rental (figuratively).

• Contact owner through Car Details - Checking out a ride you like? Jump start straight from Car Details to Messages, and let the owner know you'd like to take the car for a spin (again, figuratively. Save the doughnuts for the gas station).

Version 2.0.0

’Tis the season for sharing, car sharing that is! With a brand new release, it’s about time to unwrap your improved SnappCar App.

• The biggest gift of all, apart from that X-mas sweater mum made you, is a fully supported account verification. No more switching between web and app, just stay right here :).

• A new tool for uploading your driving license. It’s so nice, you can do it twice: front and backside of your license please.

• Okay there’s no red-nosed Rudolph to guide you through our app, but we do have puppy-eyed Niek who designed awesome notifications that will help you set up your account.

• Want to impress your friends that you’re about to rent a Toyota Prius? This is your chance. Share the details of your rental through e-mail, WhatsApp, Facebook etc. (No offense to Prius owners)

• Set the rental period and we’ll list the total amount of free kilometers you get. Great for calculating how to pay Santa a visit for free.

• Overall stability and performance improvements, we won’t bother you with the super technical details.

Version 2.1.0

• Better filters - Looking for that special one? Car, we mean. Then go ahead and use the new and improved filters: they’re slicker than a car salesman, faster than a Bugatti, and pretty much unbreakable. We said "pretty much".

• Push notifications - Push it to the limit. LIIIIMIIIIT. Did your request get accepted, or did you receive the payment for your rental? We’ll notify you with a push for a number of (relevant) reasons so you can get straight to car sharing.

• Deeplinks - Excuse me? Deeplinking. It’s when you get one of our texts or emails with a link, you click it (of course) and it takes you straight to our websi... - NOT ANYMORE - it takes you straight to the right screen in our app. That’s what we call a smooth ride.

Version 2.2.0

• Reviews - Honest reviews lead to more trust within the community. Tell the owner how you experienced your last rental by giving them a review.

• View other profiles - Get to know the community and check out the profiles of other members. You might share a common interest - like cats for example... Or cars.

• New profile features - Do you remember Pimp My Ride? We’ve made Pimp My Profile. Go ahead and add or edit; your phone number (quite handy for getting in touch with owners or renters), your profile picture, and share your life’s (short) story in the About Me section.

Version 2.2.1

• Performance & stability improvements

Version 2.2.0

• Reviews - Honest reviews lead to more trust within the community. Tell the owner how you experienced your last rental by giving them a review.

• View other profiles - Get to know the community and check out the profiles of other members. You might share a common interest - like cats for example... Or cars.

• New profile features - Do you remember Pimp My Ride? We’ve made Pimp My Profile. Go ahead and add or edit; your phone number (quite handy for getting in touch with owners or renters), your profile picture, and share your life’s (short) story in the About Me section.

Version 2.3.0

• New renting out section - A wonderful new world within the app ready for you to explore. You can view and manage your cars, car details, pricing, and set pick-up and drop-off times.

• Update your calendar - Do you love the colour green? Well we just gave you about 31 opportunities to use it. Check out the all new calendar and update your availability.

• Separated bookings - The moment for springtime cleaning is here! So we tidied up our app. All renter bookings are now placed in the renting section and the owner bookings in the renting out section. So fresh, so clean.

• Instant Booking for owners - Always wanted to be a lightning quick superhero? This is your time to shine. Become the Flash! Turn on Instant Booking (the lightning icon) in the renting out section and rent out your car faster than any spandex-wearing person can run.

• Switch between renting and renting out - Do you live the SnappCar double life? Renter by day, owner by night? Unlike Superman, changing your appearance doesn't require a phone-booth. Just your phone. With the touch of a button in the app you will easily switch from renting to renting out. That's what we call Super.

Version 2.4

• We added cruise control in our SnappCar app! We improved the process for sending a rental request to give you more control over the details, for example with Instant Booking and Cross-border coverage.

Version 2.4.1

• New Photos section - Does your car look great today? From now on you can easily edit your car photos.

Version 2.4

• We added cruise control in our SnappCar app! We improved the process for sending a rental request to give you more control over the details, for example with Instant Booking and Cross-border coverage.

Version 2.5.0

• Add a new car: Sharing is car-ing! Easily add a new car straight from the app, create your car profile, set your pricing and your car is ready to hit the road.

• Price overview: "Would you like a receipt?" Not necessary anymore, you'll find your expenses in the price overview in your Booking Details.

• SnappCar Direct: There is no need to do the key handover anymore! With a SnappCar Direct car the renter can easily open the car with our app. You can recognize these cars by the icon and or use the filter options.

• Owner of a SnappCar Direct car? From now on you only need your fingertips to open and close the car or check the location.

Version 2.6.0

• New and improved Messages: sending messages with the speed of a Tesla! It’s never been so easy to stay in touch with your renter of car owner.

• Check-in/Check-out Summary: Open your app and go to Booking Details... Isn’t that great? You can view the details of the check-in and check-out in the summary!

• 'Not allowed' preferences: Not allowed to smoke in the car or to go abroad? Check the Car Details and you’ll see the 'Not allowed' preferences directly on your screen.

• Reorganised Profile screen: Looking for some specific information? You'll definitely find it in our brand new reorganised Profile screen.

• Leave feedback: Do you have something on your mind? We're glad to offer you a listening ear - and email address - for all your feedback and questions.

• Private Lease: Looking for a cool car but also want to contribute to the environment? Read more about our unique private lease deal in the app!

Version 2.7.0

• Improved calendar: Both pending and accepted bookings are now marked in the calendar, with a blue or orange color respectively. Selecting a date range will also show you how many bookings you will have in this period and you can tap them to see the booking details. We also added a 7-day calendar overview for your convenience.

• Improved push notifications: You’ll see more details like date and time of the rental request and how much you can earn. By using a Long-Press you can also reply on a message without opening the app, and as an owner you can either accept or view the booking. As a bonus, we also added a custom sound, honk honk!

• Damages section: The damages section in the Car Settings will allow you to check the current damages whenever you want. You can also add new damages to keep the list up-to-date.

• What’s Next section: After sending a rental request we show you the next steps so you know what to expect and when. Including a pro tip, send more rental request to increase the chance to get a car.

• GDPR updates: not as sexy as all the other things we did, but still very important because we value your privacy.

Version 2.8.0

• Add bookings to your calendar: Easily keep track of all your SnappCar bookings. Confirmed bookings can now be added to your Apple calendar by the tap of a button. If you use a different calendar, please use the calendar attachment in the email.

• Improved calendar: We’ve improved the calendar you use the choose your rental period. It’s easier to see when a car is available and you can choose both a date range and pick-up and drop-off times in one go.

Version 2.9.0

• Reporting: You are now able help our Community Support team to monitor any undesired activity to ensure a safe SnappCar community. Help our efforts by reporting suspicious or inappropriate activity on a person’s profile, car, request, review or messages. To report something:
- Profiles: Tap the ‘Report this user’ link on the bottom of the profile
- Car: Tap the ‘Report this car’ link on the bottom of the profile
- Request: Tap the ‘Report this request’ link on the bottom of the profile
- Review: Long press on the review you want to report and tap the ‘Report’ bubble.
- Message: Long press on the message you want to report and tap the ‘Report’ bubble.

• Booking number: We’ve added the booking number to the Booking Overview and Booking Details. This will make it easier to find a specific booking when you’ve Snapped a car from the same person or when in contact with our Community Support.

• Performance and stability improvements

Version 3.0.0

• Onboarding: We've rolled out the red carpet for everyone that's new to SnappCar and we make sure you get the 5-star treatment. We'll show you the way around our app, the benefits of using SnappCar and how renting or renting out works.

• Your safety is our priority: To guarantee a safe and secure booking experience we've added several reminders throughout the app to please keep all communication and payments within the SnappCar platform.

• Ready for iOS 12: We made sure our app is compatible with iOS 12 so you can have the best SnappCar experience on the latest iOS version as well.

Version 3.1.0

• Performance overview: Per popular demand we added an overview to track your performance for renting out on SnappCar. You can view how much you earned, total amount of bookings and review score as well as how you are performing in terms of response time and response rate. See how you can improve your performance in order to get more bookings.

• Preparation time: Preparation time is the amount of time you need between a received rental request and the start of a booking. When you need less preparation time, you increase the chances of getting more bookings. You can set the preparation time in your car preferences by accessing the Car Details.

• Recurring availability period: You can now use recurring periods in the availability calendar to set your cars’ availability to either available or unavailable for a recurring day or group of days, e.g. when your car is available only in the weekends or unavailable for a certain day of the week.

• Verification status: We made it easier for you to check which users are verified by SnappCar to rent a car or rent out their car. You can check the verification status of another user on their profile, which will help you make the right decision.

Version 3.2.0

• Redesign: Sometimes you need to fix some stuff under the hood, and other times you just want to apply a new paint job to give you car a fresh look. We did exactly that with the app, we redesigned the check-in and check-out, booking overview and booking details. The new design makes it much easier to find important information about your rentals, we hope you like it!

• Preview car: We love feedback! Many of you asked for a way to preview your car, to see how it will be visible in searches from renters, and now you can. Tap Preview in the top right corner on the Car details.

• Share your car: Bonus! You are now also able to easily share your SnappCar listing with the rest of the world. Tap the Share icon when previewing your car.

Version 3.2.2

• Stability and performance improvement

• Stability and performance improvement

Version 3.3.0

• Keyless Information: SnappCar Keyless allows your to rent out your car more frequently without any hassle. You can now read more about it in the app!

• Keyless Fuel Step Reminder: For our Keyless cars, we added an extra step in the check-in/out to remind our beloved renters to refuel the car before br

• Payout Reminder: We noticed that some owners do not have their bank information in their profile. That makes it super hard for us to transfer the piles of well deserved SnappMoneys. We now send reminders to owners to enter this information.

• Payout explanation: We added information to tell owners when they (with their freshly entered IBAN) can expect SnappCar money to become money in the bank.

• Technology update: We updated to the latest XC and Swift versions. You probably know just as well as me what those are, but our developer ensures me that these are very good things.

• Bug Fixes: We fixed some nasty little bugs that sneaked into the check-in flow. They apologized, we threw them out of the car and you’ll never see them again.

Version 3.4.0

• Prompt for profile image: SnappCar is all about trust. What’s a better way to achieve online trust by having an online face? We now send you a reminder if you forgot to add a profile picture.

• Default address search: when you open the app, back for the very first time, we prefill your address in search to make it Snappy from the start.

• Review text is optional: to stimulate the number of reviews, writing a text is now optional. As long as you give five stars, everybody is happy!

• Review at the end of checkout: to further motivate reviews, we added a nifty little step at the end of a rental checkout where you can go ahead and leave a shining review right away.

• Review reminders: even with the optional text and the review step at checkout, you forgot to leave a review. Don’t worry! We’ll honk the horn and remind you to leave one after a day or so.

• Badges for chat on the app: you already saw a badge on your SnappCar app when you had an outstanding rental request, but we’ll now also update the counter if you have unread chat messages. Missed chats, be gone!

• Tech talk: in the previous update, the developers convinced me that updating Swift was great. Now they said we added logging to catch bugs faster. Sounds good! I really dislike bugs, so it’s a go!
